SEVERAL people were injured in a N3 westbound car crash in Cato Ridge on Sunday, 16 May. When Meditech emergency and rescue workers arrived on the scene, they said a car travelling against the traffic on the N3 had smashed head-on into another vehicle, resulting in multiple cars crashing. According to Arrive Alive, when paramedics arrived on the scene, they found numerous people hurt. It was also found that one driverâ€™s injuries were fatal and he was declared dead on the scene. All injured patients were stabilised before being transported to the hospital for further medical care. All authorities were on the scene and will be conducting a full investigation into the incident. 